notes.note:
Hi Amritpal, 
I have completed the GAP calculation for your GAP claim. Unfortunately, there is no eligible GAP claim payout. 
As per your contract, there is no coverage for any missed, deferred or unpaid payments on your automobile loan. Your outstanding loan amount on the date of loss was $38448.09, but when we re-amortize your loan, your outstanding loan amount on the date of loss should have been $38155.45. We also look at the amount that the insurance company provided as your settlement. In your scenario, your insurance company provides you with a GST credit that is available to you when you purchase a new vehicle. This amount has to be deducted from your GAP claim as it is funds that are available to you. This puts you in a negative scenario, as the insurance company provided you with more than what the outstanding loan amount should have been. Please see the below calculation:
$38155.45 - $37430.43 - $1772.45 = -$1047.43
At this time, your GAP claim has been closed as there is nothing that we are able to payout. I apologize for the inconvenience. 
Please let me know if you have any questions. 
Thank you, 
Sarah Gabor
